description:
In this episode of ANN Profiles, the original host of this podcast and assistant director of communication for the General Conference (GC) of Seventh-day Adventists, Alyssa Truman, takes on the role of the interviewee and engages in a conversation with Sam Neves about her unique journey from learning and creativity during her childhood to leading major communication initiatives for the Adventist World Church.  Alyssa opens up about the struggles and triumphs of her life, her deep-seated passion for ministry, and how embracing her creative talents led to her current role. Hear this story of resilience, faith, and the power of embracing one's calling.

The Seventh-day Adventist Church has been an established denomination since 1863. It is a global Christian family with over 21 million members who hold the Bible as the ultimate authority. We are believers who promise to help people understand the Bible to find freedom, healing, and hope in Jesus.
